# AI Assistant Instructions

See `CLAUDE.md` for the full development guide — project structure, conventions, agent roles, code review checklist, and key contracts.

## Platform Quick-Reference

### TypeScript / Next.js
- App router and server components
- Strict mode; no `any` without justification
- async/await; no raw promise chains

### Firebase
- Handle quota limits and rate limiting explicitly
- All writes that require validation go through the function layer, never direct from client
- Security rules must be updated alongside any data model change

### Swift / iOS
- Swift naming conventions
- Modern concurrency: async/await, actors
- SwiftUI best practices; no UIKit bridging unless unavoidable
